{"word":"ἀνθίστημι","slug":"ἀνθίστημι","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἀνθίστημι</b></el> <p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to set against</i>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b>: <i>to set up in opposition</i>, <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>to match with, compare</i>, <b><a href='S:Plutarch'>Plut.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a>, with <a href='S:intransitive'>intr.</a> aor2 <a href='S:active signification'><a href='S:Active voice'>act.</a></a> <el>ἀντέστην</el>, <a href='S:perfect tense'>perf.</a> <el>ἀνθέστηκα</el>, attic <a href='S:contracted, contraction'>contr.</a> <a href='S:participle'>part.</a> <el>ἀνθεστώς</el>: <a href='S:future tense'>fut.</a> <a href='S:Medium, Middle'>mid.</a> <el>ἀντιστήσομαι</el>, aor1 <el>ἀντεστησάμην</el> and <a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>pass.</a></a> <el>ἀντεστάθην [α]</el>:— <i>to stand against</i>, <a href='S:especially'>esp.</a> in battle, <i>to withstand, oppose</i>, <el>τινι</el> <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, attic; also, <el>πρός τινα</el> <b><a href='S:Thucydides'>Thuc.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>: rarely <a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:genitive'>gen.</a>, <el>φρενῶν ἀνθίσταται</el> (al. <el>ἀνθάπτεται</el>) <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><a href='S:absolute, absolutely'>absol.</a> <i>to make a stand</i>, <b><a href='S:Iliad'>Il.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}